Species in Alpine lakes

Lakes Walen and Zurichesse

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=WZ
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/Walen.txt \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/Zurich.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

Admixture analysis with variant K

We define the K parameter from 2 to 4, computing the cross-validation error. Then, we extract these values.


INPUT='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-09/admixture/ALPINE/WZ.bed'

for K in 2 3 4; do 
  if [ ! -e log${K}.WZ.out ]; then
    admixture --cv $INPUT $K | tee log${K}.WZ.out; 
  fi 
done
    
grep -h CV log*.WZ.out

## CV error (K=2): 0.48759
## CV error (K=3): 0.53744
## CV error (K=4): 0.66391

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=BT_all
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/BT_all.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

Admixture analysis with variant K

We define the K parameter from 4 to 6, computing the cross-validation error. Then, we extract these values.


INPUT='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-09/admixture/ALPINE/BT_all.bed'

for K in 4 5 6; do 
  if [ ! -e log${K}.BT_all.out ]; then
    admixture --cv $INPUT $K | tee log${K}.BT_all.out; 
  fi 
done
    
grep -h CV log*.BT_all.out

if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/BT_afap.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

INPUT='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-09/admixture/ALPINE/BT_afap.bed'

  if [ ! -e log${K}.BT_afap.out ]; then

  fi 
done

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=BT_afa
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/BT_afa.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=BT_afs
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/BT_afs.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=BT_af
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/BT_af.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=ALL
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/ADMX/ALL.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0

Data selecting and filtering

VCF='/gata/mar/cophyhopa/results/2022-05-04/assem2_indv2.recode.vcf'
FILE=ARC
if [ ! -e $FILE.vcf.gz ]; then
   vcftools --vcf $VCF \
            --out dirty \
            --keep ~/cophyhopa/data/Arctic.txt \
            --recode \
            --recode-INFO-all
   vcftools --vcf dirty.recode.vcf \
            --out $FILE \
            --thin 500 \
            --remove-indels \
            --mac 2 \
            --max-alleles 2 \
            --max-meanDP 1000 \
            --max-missing-count 7 \
            --stdout \
            --recode --recode-INFO-all \
            | gzip > $FILE.vcf.gz
fi
if [ -e dirty.recode.vcf ]; then rm dirty.recode.vcf; fi

if [ ! -e chromMap.txt ]; then
   gunzip -c $FILE".vcf.gz" | \
   gawk '(/^[^#]/){
      A[$1] = 1
   }END{
      N = 1
      for (chr in A) {
         print chr "\t" N
         N = N + 1
      }
   }' > chromMap.txt
fi

vcftools --gzvcf $FILE".vcf.gz" \
         --plink --mac 2 --remove-indels --max-alleles 2 \
         --chrom-map chromMap.txt \
         --out $FILE

gawk -v OFS="\t" '{
   $1 = 1
   $2 = 1 ":" $4
   print $0
}' $FILE".map" > better.map
mv better.map $FILE.map

plink --file $FILE --make-bed --out $FILE --allow-no-sex --allow-extra-chr 0
